{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/diagnosis/diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"213ffb47-21f3-57b4-96c0-c3a3036c0817","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 35aa24e1-ccc7-435f-9819-6b751ceb2b30 --><h2>How should I make a diagnosis of plantar fasciitis?</h2><!-- end field 35aa24e1-ccc7-435f-9819-6b751ceb2b30 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 723582af-6f2a-41ca-ae62-e5fbd692e9c8 --><!-- begin field 1f0dba9e-a24e-48b5-830a-b7bb69fbd335 --><p><strong>Plantar fasciitis is usually diagnosed by the history and physical examination findings alone. </strong></p><ul><li><strong>Ask about the nature of the heel pain, and the general health and physical activity of the person.</strong><ul><li>Characteristic symptoms of plantar fasciitis include:<ul><li>An initial insidious onset of heel pain.</li><li>Intense heel pain during the first steps after waking or after a period of inactivity, with relief upon initiation of movement.</li><li>Pain that reduces with moderate activity, but worsens later during the day or after long periods of standing or walking.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Document any <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/background-information/causes-risk-factors/\">risk factors</a>, </strong>such as age between 40–60 years, overweight or obesity, running, or prolonged standing or walking.</li><li><strong>Examine the foot at rest (when sitting) and when standing and walking. </strong>Signs of plantar fasciitis include:<ul><li>Tenderness on palpation of the plantar heel area (particularly, but not always, localized around the medial calcaneal tuberosity).</li><li>Limited ankle dorsiflexion range (with the knee in extension).</li><li>Positive 'Windlass test' (reproduction of pain by extension of the first metatarsophalangeal joint).</li><li>Tightness of the Achilles tendon.</li><li>An antalgic gait (abnormal walking to avoid pain) or limping.</li></ul></li><li><strong>If clinical features of plantar fasciitis are absent or inconsistent, </strong>consider an <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/\">alternative diagnosis</a>.<strong> </strong><ul><li>If the diagnosis is uncertain, referral to a podiatrist or orthopaedic surgeon for further investigation (depending on the suspicion of the cause) may be necessary.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 1f0dba9e-a24e-48b5-830a-b7bb69fbd335 --><!-- end item 723582af-6f2a-41ca-ae62-e5fbd692e9c8 -->","topic":{"id":"0a10c518-b918-58bc-8764-7c4350a0b285","topicId":"04fa42cb-b715-4bdd-b68b-077d525fb94e","topicName":"Plantar fasciitis","slug":"plantar-fasciitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in March 2020","chapters":[{"id":"806e768f-9d38-5b21-ad33-68c36c700d3f","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ffc55535-2f91-5791-8574-d8cf527fc9da","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"69dfec13-e4fc-59f4-9147-eceb3cff5f47","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"29d42675-e683-52a9-aa63-b5902436041e","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"7bdc1eff-73fc-5edc-ab5b-0d67de4265c6","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"5548137c-18b3-574c-9067-390620d5bc89","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"100f78de-d0ae-53b1-a32d-f100d3b4d50c","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"8c96fd2d-949c-55d1-8578-d45ec2776453","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"72c3c0b1-b4a2-505e-961f-320af392d4ef","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"2d45a239-c659-5e74-bc1b-687d3003f41d","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"74fbc659-8c2e-5eb9-9ce9-846a8fc73377","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"6918b254-20ca-5065-b3c5-a31321f9c243","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"a4150890-94fd-51c3-afc7-87619a111484","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"563f620c-0094-5d95-9c91-21a5929de29c","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"acc8f41b-f9a5-5ac2-bacd-54c1b1a122db","slug":"causes-risk-factors","fullItemName":"Causes and risk factors"},{"id":"6e41189f-178a-57ee-af0c-864c6bd569e5","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"e432d9b7-39af-5bbd-957e-978dd67d5f85","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"5df0025c-c8ec-54be-8830-44f8fb72a5e1","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"213ffb47-21f3-57b4-96c0-c3a3036c0817","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"5c465b77-66e9-5252-ba6c-7a42d61a6b3a","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"2fa45733-3368-566e-850e-a1f423ec0057","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"3b3153bf-c9ea-54de-b775-46516c662208","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"3777fe59-06e5-5789-ae37-7ce7414ba31c","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9fe41f3b-fe80-5c29-b02b-4e57481dfb13","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"f757ba13-0f15-5cd5-9b69-89e131cc553d","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"b097e19b-743c-5834-a2ad-84ad0e401dd9","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"0766ce8f-6ef2-5050-8c8c-43b3ffbc3109","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"94222c3e-3588-5c99-ac76-4aff6da69285","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"28c7b61a-1025-58cc-ad00-bf058b88cae3","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"f9bfccf3-8463-5922-a2cc-e8f8a9bad827","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"5df0025c-c8ec-54be-8830-44f8fb72a5e1","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"bdf7fe2d-b45a-50b5-9c69-91288c46c3cf","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-56b","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field ac64ce2f-e293-494a-885a-f57e8f5c05db --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field ac64ce2f-e293-494a-885a-f57e8f5c05db -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 56bedc83-25d8-4225-8d5a-8cddb77f0961 --><!-- begin field 69eca8cc-2880-44ca-b0bb-d94002892cdc --><p>These recommendations are based on the <em>American College of Foot and Ankle Surgeons Clinical Consensus Statement: Diagnosis and Treatment of Adult Acquired Infracalcaneal Heel Pain </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/references/\">Schneider, 2018</a>] and on<em> </em>expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/references/\">Orchard, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/references/\">Thing et al, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/references/\">Becker, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/references/\">Luffy, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/references/\">BMJ, 2019</a>].</p><ul><li>Plantar fasciitis is diagnosed, in most cases, by the history and physical examination findings alone. Routine use of X-rays is not necessary for the diagnosis of non-traumatic plantar fasciitis. Advanced imaging, such as ultrasound scan and magnetic resonance imaging, is not necessary for the diagnosis or guidance of treatment of non-traumatic plantar fasciitis [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/plantar-fasciitis/references/\">Schneider, 2018</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 69eca8cc-2880-44ca-b0bb-d94002892cdc --><!-- end item 56bedc83-25d8-4225-8d5a-8cddb77f0961 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}